<br>
The Rights laid out in the constitution are one of the most important things to Americans.  Without those rights we simply would not be.  We would still be a colonial lacky (sorry canada).  Taking away an Americans rights is like taking away our oxygen.  We can't live without it.  <br>
<br>
Our right to bear arms is one of the fundamental ideas that America was built upon.  Is it antiquated?  Sure you bet, but the idea still holds true.  Because it was written down on a piece of Parchment and signed by our founding fathers.  To Americans that parchment is more holy then any bible.  To rip that part out of our Constitution would be like ripping the the part about Christ dying on the Cross for our sins out of the bible.  The meaning of the whole story would be lost.<br>
<br>
